sublicensed, embedded in hardware products, incorporated into commercial
products, and redistributed in source or binary form.

No source-code disclosure obligations are imposed by this License.

2. External File Service Restriction

An Organization whose Annual Revenue exceeds USD $50,000,000 may not Operate
an External File Service for External Users using the Software without a
separate written license from ExNimbus LLC.

This restriction applies regardless of whether the External File Service is a
primary feature, secondary feature, ancillary feature, incidental feature,
managed-service component, backup or synchronization feature, appliance
feature, platform feature, or other component of a product or service.

3. Internal Infrastructure Exception

Notwithstanding Section 2, an Organization may use the Software as an internal
infrastructure component, including to store, process, manage, replicate, back
up, archive, or transfer data associated with customers, clients, partners, or
other third parties, provided that such third parties do not receive
file-access functionality from the Software.

4. Internal Use Exception

The restriction in Section 2 does not apply to Internal Use.

"Internal Use" means use solely by:

* employees of the Organization;
* contractors acting on behalf of the Organization;
* parent entities of the Organization;
* subsidiaries of the Organization; and
* entities under common control with the Organization.

Internal Use is permitted regardless of Annual Revenue.

5. Customer Self-Hosting Exception

Notwithstanding Section 2, an Organization may distribute, sublicense, sell, or
otherwise provide the Software to a Customer for the Customer to install and
operate in the Customer's own environment, provided that the Organization does
not Operate the resulting External File Service for that Customer or for that
Customer's External Users.

Providing ordinary support, consulting, implementation assistance,
configuration assistance, documentation, updates, or security fixes does not,
by itself, mean that an Organization Operates an External File Service.
Hosting, administering, managing, controlling, or making available the External
File Service for a Customer does mean that the Organization Operates that
External File Service.

6. Definitions

"Annual Revenue" means the consolidated gross revenue of an Organization and
all entities controlling, controlled by, or under common control with that
Organization during the most recently completed fiscal year. For governmental,
educational, non-profit, or other entities that do not report gross revenue,
Annual Revenue means the closest equivalent annual operating revenue, receipts,
or budget. If Annual Revenue is reported in a currency other than U.S. dollars,
convert it using a reasonable published exchange rate for the last day of the
relevant fiscal year. If an Organization has not completed a fiscal year, use a
reasonable good-faith estimate for the current fiscal year.

For purposes of calculating Annual Revenue and applying Section 2, an
Organization includes any predecessor, successor, spin-off, divested business
unit, reorganization vehicle, affiliate, or entity formed, separated, funded,
licensed, managed, controlled, operated, or used for the purpose of avoiding
the Annual Revenue threshold or External File Service restriction.

A divested, spun-off, or reorganized entity must include the Annual Revenue of
the entity, business unit, or assets from which it was separated for the fiscal
year in which the separation occurs and the following fiscal year, unless that
entity is not controlled by, under common control with, funded primarily by,
operated primarily for the benefit of, or contractually restricted for the
benefit of the prior controlling Organization.

"Control" means the direct or indirect power to direct or cause the direction
of the management or policies of an entity, whether through ownership of voting
securities, by contract, or otherwise. Control includes ownership of more than
50% of the voting interests of an entity.

"Customer" means a person or entity that receives the Software, or a product
or service containing the Software, from an Organization.

"External File Service" means file-storage, file-hosting, file-sharing,
file-synchronization, network file access, SMB access, backup storage, or
substantially similar file-access functionality made available to External
Users.

"External User" means a person or entity that is not within the Organization's
Internal Use group.

"Operate" means to host, run, administer, manage, control, or make available a
service or system. An Organization Operates a service even if the service is
provided through a hosted product, managed service, appliance, cloud service,
support service, outsourcing arrangement, or other offering.

"Organization" means an individual, corporation, partnership, limited liability
company, governmental entity, non-profit entity, educational institution, or
other legal person.

